answers.body_markdown:
You are reading the data twice. One with `file_get_contents` and others with `fread`. No need for that. I guess you want the 4th MB, and the last MB, and the hash of the whole file to be inserted to the database. You can do it this way:

    // set filename to a variable
    $filename = &quot;mydata.zip&quot;;
    // open the file for reading
    $f = fopen($filename, &quot;r&quot;);
    // set the cursor position where the 3rd MB ends
    fseek($f, 3 * 1024 * 1024, SEEK_SET);
    // read 1MB of data
    $first = fread($f, 1024);
    // set the cursor position to the start of last MB
    fseek($f, -1024, SEEK_END);
    // read 1MB of data
    $last = fread($f, 1024);
    // get the hash of the file    
    $hash = md5($file);

